<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include("partials/header") %>

<body class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
  <%- include("partials/nav") %>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <section class="rounded-xl p-8 border-slate-700">
      <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:flex-row items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">How PixelPicks Works</p>
          <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About PixelPicks</h1>

          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300">
            Right now everybody is bored, stressed, and presented with endless choices of games to play.
            Choosing the right game to spend hours of your time on can be a complex endeavor, and has many
            factors involved such as the cost, story, gameplay, art, and technical design.

            <br><br>PixelPicks uses a decision matrix with several criteria from 1 (worst) to
            10 (best) to find the game best for your next playthrough. Higher values correlate
            to a higher performance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="m-2 flex flex-col justify-center items-center max-w-sm rounded-full">
          <img src="images/questionmark.jpg" alt="My profile picture." class="rounded-full p-5 border border-green-400">
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-6 border-1 border-slate-700">

      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">Criteria</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Decision Criteria</h1>

      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300">
        The criteria by which PixelPicks judges games.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 mt-5">
        <% data.criteria.forEach(function(criterion) { %>
          <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900 transition
          transition-time-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-slate-800">
            <label for="<%= criterion.id %>" class="block font-semibold mb-1 text-xl">
              <%= criterion.name %>
            </label>

            <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400">
              <%= criterion.description %>
            </p>
          </div>
        <% }); %>
        <a href="/tool" class="flex items-center justify-center text-white font-semibold p-4 rounded-lg
        bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-center text-xl">
          Try PixelPicks →
        </a>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-6 border-1 border-slate-700">

      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">Methods</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Weighting Methods</h1>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
        <div class="flex-1 border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900 transition transition-time-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-slate-800">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Weighted Sum<p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400">
            Weighted sum multiplies each criteria by a normalized weight, then sums them all together.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm bg-slate-600 rounded shadow">
            score = (score1 x weight1) + ... + (scoreN x weightN)
          </code>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400 mt-2">
            Simplest method, takes a weighted average across all criteria.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900 transition transition-time-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-slate-800">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Weighted Product<p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400">
            Weighted product multiplies all the criteria together exponentiated to their weight.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm bg-slate-600 rounded shadow">
            score = score1^weight1 x ... x scoreN^weightN
          </code>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400 mt-2">
            Rewards games that are higher across multiple categories.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-6 border-1 border-slate-700">

      <% const storyCriterionName = data.criteria.find(function (c) { return c.id === "story"; }).name; %>

      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">Example</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">When the Method Changes the Winner</h1>

      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300">
        The two methods don't always agree on a winner. Below, the same two games are weighted with the
        same weights.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 mt-5">
        <% exampleSumResults.forEach(function(game) { %>
          <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900">
            <p class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2"><%= game.name %></p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-sm text-slate-400">
              <% data.criteria.forEach(function(criterion) { %>
                <p><%= criterion.name %>: <span class="text-slate-200"><%= game.scores[criterion.id] %>/10</span></p>
              <% }); %>
            </div>
          </div>
        <% }); %>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 mt-5">
        <div class="flex-1 border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900">
          <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">Weighted Sum Winner</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2"><%= exampleSumResults[0].name %></p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900">
          <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">Weighted Product Winner</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2"><%= exampleProductResults[0].name %></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300 mt-5">
        The winner flips because <%= exampleSumResults[0].name %> only has an average
        <%= storyCriterionName %> score, and weighted sum just averages contributions. So, being
        strong everywhere else is enough to win. Weighted product instead raises every score to its
        weight and multiplies them together, so while <%= exampleProductResults[0].name %>'s perfect
        <%= storyCriterionName %> score shields it from that penalty, even though it is weaker in
        other criteria. Weighted sum rewards high scores across all criteria, while weighted product
        punishes weak scores in criteria.
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <a href="/tool" class="flex items-center justify-center text-white font-semibold p-4 rounded-lg
            bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-center text-xl">
          Try PixelPicks →
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include("partials/footer") %>
</body>
</html>
